GritQL is a declarative query language for searching and modifying source code.

- üìñ Start simply without learning AST details: any code snippet is a valid GritQL query
- ‚ö°Ô∏è Use Rust and query optimization to scale up to 10M+ line repositories
- üì¶ Use Grit's built-in module system to reuse 200+ [standard patterns](https://github.com/getgrit/stdlib) or [share your own](https://docs.grit.io/guides/sharing#anchor-publishing-patterns)
- ‚ôªÔ∏è Once you learn GritQL, you can use it to rewrite any [target language](https://docs.grit.io/language/target-languages): JavaScript/TypeScript, Python, JSON, Java, Terraform, Solidity, CSS, Markdown, YAML, Rust, Go, or SQL
- üîß GritQL makes it easy to include auto-fix rules for faster remediation

